Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1} into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Halve
@celery{2.5%ounce} lengthwise; dice into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Drain and rinse
@cannellini beans{1%can} and @kidney beans{1%can}. Roughly chop
@parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pot{} over medium heat.
Add onion, celery, @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}
(you'll use the rest in the next step), a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and
@pepper{to taste}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and
lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> If onion browns too quickly, add a splash of water and lower heat.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2},
@Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce can}, half the
cannellini beans, half the kidney beans, @water{2%cups}, and a big pinch of
salt and pepper.

> Use all the cannellini and kidney beans and 4 cups water for 4 servings.

Increase heat to medium high and bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a
low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans and couscous are tender,
~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise; slice each half lengthwise into
thirds.

In a large #bowl{}, toss baguette pieces with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{large drizzle}, remaining garlic powder, and salt and pepper to
taste until evenly coated. Arrange seasoned baguette pieces on a #baking sheet{}
and bake on top rack until lightly toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove baking sheet from oven; carefully flip breadsticks and return to top
rack until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Divide soup between bowls; garnish with parsley. Serve with breadsticks on
the side.